<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 9:45AM CDT  by NWS San Angelo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Crockett County through 1015 AM CDT...
At 943 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles south of Ozona, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Highway 163 And Ranch Road 1973.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
